 {
  "uid": "arxiv:2607.15414v1",
  "drop": false,
  "field": "finance",
  "role": "agent",
  "bullets": [
   "Five large language models evaluated on four technical-analysis tasks using OHLCV price data and financial reports; sample period and market coverage not stated, benchmarked against a passive S&P 500 strategy.",
   "GPT-4 Turbo, Claude 3 Opus, Gemini 1.5 Pro, Llama 3 70B, and domain-tuned FinGPT generate buy/sell/hold signals and read reports, scored with F1, BLEU, and simulated backtest risk metrics.",
   "GPT-4 Turbo posts the highest annualized return and Sharpe ratio among general models and FinGPT trails closely; both beat the S&P 500, but all models show numerical hallucination and weak sideways-market performance."
  ],
  "bullet_provenance": "ai",
